<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>This page will be updated as new advice becomes available.</p>

<h2 id="prison-social-visits-in-england-and-wales">Prison social visits in England and Wales</h2>

<div class="call-to-action">
<p>In response to new restrictions in Wales, visits to Welsh prisons will be suspended from 18:00 on Friday 23 October. There may be exceptions for visits to young adults (HMP Parc), or on compassionate grounds which should be agreed in advance with the establishment prior to travel. Please <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/prisons-in-england-and-wales" class="govuk-link">check with the prison</a> for further details.
<br></br><br></br>
Prisons in England are open when it is safe for visitors. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/visit-someone-in-prison-during-the-coronavirus-covid-19-pandemic" class="govuk-link">Certain restrictions apply</a> because of coronavirus (COVID-19). This means that it’s important to check local guidance regularly as the situation in individual prisons may change. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/prisons-in-england-and-wales" class="govuk-link">Find out which prisons have social visits</a>
<br></br><br></br></p>
</div>

<h2 id="local-covid-alert-levels-and-visiting-prisons">Local COVID alert levels and visiting prisons</h2>

<p>In response to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/local-covid-alert-levels-what-you-need-to-know" class="govuk-link">local COVID alert levels</a>, there may be changes to visits at some prisons.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Visitors should not book a visit or travel to a prison for a visit if they feel at all unwell. If you have <a rel="external" href="https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/coronavirus-covid-19/" class="govuk-link">symptoms of COVID-19</a> you should book a test and self-isolate in line with <a rel="external" href="https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/coronavirus-covid-19/testing-and-tracing/" class="govuk-link">NHS Test and Trace</a>.</li>
  <li>Where families or other social visitors live in a local COVID alert level area of ‘very high’ they should follow the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/local-covid-alert-levels-what-you-need-to-know#local-covid-alert-level-very-high" class="govuk-link">government advice</a> not to travel from these areas and should not try to book or travel to visit any prison within or outside that area. There may be exceptions for visits on compassionate grounds which should be agreed in advance with the establishment prior to travel.</li>
  <li>Where families or other social visitors live in a COVID alert level area of ‘medium’ or ‘high’, they should not try to book or travel to a prison in a ‘very high’ local alert area. There may be exceptions for visits on compassionate grounds which should be agreed in advance with the establishment prior to travel.</li>
  <li>All establishments will continue to monitor the ability to be able to safely hold social visits and may choose to temporarily restrict visits to some or all residents.</li>
</ul>

<p>Where face-to-face visits are temporarily suspended families can continue to <a href="#contact" class="govuk-link">stay in touch</a>.</p>

<p>Always <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/prisons-in-england-and-wales" class="govuk-link">check with the prison</a> before you book a visit to find out the latest information.</p>

<h2 id="check-before-you-visit">Check before you visit</h2>
<p>If you are travelling from a different part of the UK, for example from England to Wales, you must follow the relevant health advice of the country you are travelling to.</p>

<p>You should also not visit anyone in a prison if you are self-isolating or if you have <a rel="external" href="https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/coronavirus-covid-19/symptoms/" class="govuk-link">symptoms of COVID-19</a>. If you have symptoms of COVID-19 - a high temperature, new and persistent cough, loss or change to your sense of smell or taste - however mild, you must self-isolate for at least 10 days from when your symptoms started, or if you are not experiencing symptoms but have tested positive for COVID-19 you must self-isolate for at least 10 days starting from the day the test was taken.</p>

<p>If you have tested positive whilst not experiencing symptoms but develop symptoms during the isolation period, you must restart the 10-day isolation period from the day you develop symptoms.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/visit-someone-in-prison-during-the-coronavirus-covid-19-pandemic" class="govuk-link">Find out more about visiting someone in prison during the COVID-19 pandemic.</a></p>

<h2 id="contact">Contact someone in prison</h2>

<p>If you are unable to visit someone in prison, you can contact them by:</p>

<ul>
  <li>leaving a voice message using the <a rel="external" href="https://prisonvoicemail.com/" class="govuk-link">Prison Voicemail Service</a>
</li>
  <li>sending an email using the <a rel="external" href="https://www.emailaprisoner.com/" class="govuk-link">email a prisoner</a> service</li>
  <li>
<a href="https://www.gov.uk/staying-in-touch-with-someone-in-prison" class="govuk-link">writing to them</a>.</li>
</ul>

<p>Additional temporary secure phone handsets were issued to all prisons that did not have in-cell telephony installed. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/staying-in-touch-with-someone-in-prison" class="govuk-link">More on telephone calls.</a></p>

<p>Many prisons and young offender institutions (YOI) across England and Wales have secure video calling. More prisons and YOI will provide this in the future. Video calls are currently free for both prisoners and their families. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/visit-a-prisoner-using-a-video-call" class="govuk-link">Find out which prisons and institutions have video calling.</a></p>

<h2 id="what-we-are-doing-to-keep-people-safe-in-prisons">What we are doing to keep people safe in prisons</h2>

<p>Prisons are working with public health and NHS services and continue to prioritise the safety of staff, prisoners and visitors.</p>

<p>Prisons have procedures to manage outbreaks of infectious diseases and are prepared if cases are identified. Plans are in place for dealing with staff absences if staff working in prisons need to self-isolate.</p>

<p>Handwashing facilities are available to prisoners, staff and visitors and we have worked closely with suppliers to ensure the supply of soap and cleaning materials.</p>

<h2 id="changes-to-regimes">Changes to regimes</h2>

<p>As restrictions are eased in the community, we are safely and steadily reintroducing activities into prisons. Many prisons are re-introducing social visits and increasing access to other activities. All prisons are different and they may not all open up the same activities at the same time. We appreciate families and prisoners are keen to see all activities introduced and this is our aim, but we must progress safely.</p>

<p>This will be done wherever and whenever it is safe to do so but must also continue to follow public health advice in relation to prisons.</p>

<h2 id="parole-board-hearings-and-jury-trials">Parole Board hearings and jury trials</h2>

<p>All face-to-face Parole Board hearings have been temporarily suspended. The Parole Board will progress cases through a combination of remote hearings and a paper review process, sometimes combined with case management hearings.</p>

<p>New jury trials have started in some courts.</p>

<p>Find out more about <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/coronavirus-covid-19-courts-and-tribunals-planning-and-preparation#jury-trials" class="govuk-link">jury trials</a> and <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immediate-cancellation-of-all-face-to-face-hearings" class="govuk-link">Parole Board hearings</a>.</p>

<h2 id="how-we-will-update-you-about-the-impact-of-coronavirus-on-prisons">How we will update you about the impact of coronavirus on prisons</h2>

<p>If there are changes to the general advice for visitors or the operation of the prison system, we will update advice on this guidance page and issue updates on Twitter <a rel="external" href="https://twitter.com/hmpps" class="govuk-link">@HMPPS</a> and <a rel="external" href="https://twitter.com/MoJGovUK" class="govuk-link">@MoJGovUK</a>.</p>

<p>We also have a range of ways to communicate advice and guidance to people in prison, including <a rel="external" href="https://prison.radio/national-prison-radio/" class="govuk-link">National Prison Radio</a></p>

<h2 id="urgent-concerns-about-someone-in-prison">Urgent concerns about someone in prison</h2>

<p>If you have urgent concerns about someone in prison you should <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/prisons-in-england-and-wales" class="govuk-link">contact the prison directly.</a></p>

<h2 id="other-support-for-families">Other support for families</h2>

<h3 id="prisoners-families-helpline">Prisoners’ Families Helpline</h3>

<p><a href="mailto:info@prisonersfamilies.org" class="govuk-link">info@prisonersfamilies.org</a></p>

<p>Telephone: 0808 808 2003</p>

<p>Monday to Friday, 9am to 8pm</p>

<p>Saturday and Sunday, 10am to 3pm</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/call-charges" class="govuk-link">Find out about call charges</a></p>

<h3 id="families-outside-support-and-information-helpline">Families Outside Support and Information Helpline</h3>

<p>For prisons in Scotland only</p>

<p><a href="mailto:support@familiesoutside.org.uk" class="govuk-link">support@familiesoutside.org.uk</a></p>

<p>Telephone: 0800 254 0088</p>

<p>Monday to Friday, 9am to 5pm</p>

<p>Saturday and Sunday, Closed</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/call-charges" class="govuk-link">Find out about call charges</a></p>

<h3 id="you-can-also-get-help-and-advice-from">You can also get help and advice from:</h3>

<ul>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://www.prisonersfamilies.org/" class="govuk-link">Prisoners’ Families Helpline</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.partnersofprisoners.co.uk/" class="govuk-link">Partners of Prisoners and Families Support Group</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://www.prisonadvice.org.uk/" class="govuk-link">Prison Advice and Care Trust (PACT)</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.prisonreformtrust.org.uk/" class="govuk-link">Prison Reform Trust</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>


